  - q: "What was the longest Chinese dynasty?"
    a: "The Zhou Dynasty was the longest, lasting approximately 790 years (1046–256 BCE), though it is divided into Western Zhou (strong central authority) and Eastern Zhou (fragmented into the Spring and Autumn and Warring States periods). As a unified, effectively governed dynasty, the Han Dynasty's roughly 400 years (206 BCE–220 CE) is the strongest candidate."
