    <section id="qin">
      <h2>Qin Dynasty (<span class="chinese-char">秦朝</span>, <em>Qín Cháo</em>, 221–206 BCE)</h2>
      <p><span class="lang-en">Though lasting only 15 years, the Qin's impact was transformative. <strong>Qin Shi Huang</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">秦始皇</span>, <em>Qín Shǐhuáng</em>), the First Emperor, unified China for the first time and established the centralised imperial model that endured for over two thousand years.</span><span class="lang-tc">秦朝雖僅存15年，但其影響深遠。<strong>秦始皇</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">秦始皇</span>）首次統一中國，建立了延續兩千多年的中央集權帝國模式。</span><span class="lang-sc">秦朝虽仅存15年，但其影响深远。<strong>秦始皇</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">秦始皇</span>）首次统一中国，建立了延续两千多年的中央集权帝国模式。</span></p>
      <h3><span class="lang-en">Cultural Contributions</span><span class="lang-tc">文化貢獻</span><span class="lang-sc">文化贡献</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Standardisation</strong> — Writing (the Small Seal script, <span class="chinese-char">小篆</span>, <em>xiǎozhuàn</em>), weights, measures, currency, and axle widths were all standardised across the empire, enabling cultural unity</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>標準化</strong>——文字（小篆）、度量衡、貨幣和車軌寬度在全國統一，促成了文化統一</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>标准化</strong>——文字（小篆）、度量衡、货币和车轨宽度在全国统一，促成了文化统一</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Calendar unification</strong> — The Qin imposed a unified <a href="/calendar/">calendar</a> across the empire, establishing the Zhuanxu calendar (<span class="chinese-char">顓頊曆</span>, <em>Zhuānxū Lì</em>) with the year beginning in the 10th month</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>統一曆法</strong>——秦朝在全國推行統一的<a href="/calendar/">曆法</a>，確立了以十月為歲首的顓頊曆</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>统一历法</strong>——秦朝在全国推行统一的<a href="/calendar/">历法</a>，确立了以十月为岁首的颛顼历</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>The Terracotta Army</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">兵馬俑</span>, <em>Bīngmǎyǒng</em>) — The First Emperor's mausoleum with 8,000+ life-sized warrior figures represents the scale of Qin ambition and artistic achievement</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>兵馬俑</strong>——始皇陵中8,000多件真人大小的兵俑，展現了秦朝的宏大抱負和藝術成就</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>兵马俑</strong>——始皇陵中8,000多件真人大小的兵俑，展现了秦朝的宏大抱负和艺术成就</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong><a href="/zodiac/">Zodiac evidence</a></strong> — Bamboo slips from Shuihudi (<span class="chinese-char">睡虎地</span>, <em>Shuìhǔdì</em>, 217 BCE) contain the earliest known complete zodiac animal cycle, confirming the system was established by the Qin period</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong><a href="/zodiac/">生肖證據</a></strong>——睡虎地（<span class="chinese-char">睡虎地</span>，前217年）出土的竹簡包含已知最早的完整生肖動物周期，證實該系統在秦代已確立</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong><a href="/zodiac/">生肖证据</a></strong>——睡虎地（<span class="chinese-char">睡虎地</span>，前217年）出土的竹简包含已知最早的完整生肖动物周期，证实该系统在秦代已确立</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="han">
      <h2>Han Dynasty (<span class="chinese-char">漢朝</span>, <em>Hàn Cháo</em>, 206 BCE – 220 CE)</h2>
      <p><span class="lang-en">The Han Dynasty — divided into <strong>Western Han</strong> (206 BCE – 9 CE) and <strong>Eastern Han</strong> (25–220 CE) — established the identity of the Chinese people (who call themselves "Han" to this day). It was a period of territorial expansion, cultural confidence, and intellectual synthesis.</span><span class="lang-tc">漢朝——分為<strong>西漢</strong>（前206年–公元9年）和<strong>東漢</strong>（25–220年）——奠定了中國人的身份認同（至今仍自稱「漢人」）。這是一個領土擴張、文化自信和學術綜合的時代。</span><span class="lang-sc">汉朝——分为<strong>西汉</strong>（前206年–公元9年）和<strong>东汉</strong>（25–220年）——奠定了中国人的身份认同（至今仍自称"汉人"）。这是一个领土扩张、文化自信和学术综合的时代。</span></p>
      <h3><span class="lang-en">Cultural Contributions</span><span class="lang-tc">文化貢獻</span><span class="lang-sc">文化贡献</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Confucian state orthodoxy</strong> — Emperor Wu (<span class="chinese-char">漢武帝</span>, <em>Hàn Wǔdì</em>) established Confucianism as the official state philosophy, creating the imperial examination prototype and the scholarly class that would govern China</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>儒學正統</strong>——漢武帝（<span class="chinese-char">漢武帝</span>）確立儒學為官方國家哲學，創建了科舉制度的雛形和統治中國的士人階層</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>儒学正统</strong>——汉武帝（<span class="chinese-char">汉武帝</span>）确立儒学为官方国家哲学，创建了科举制度的雏形和统治中国的士人阶层</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Calendar reform</strong> — The Taichu calendar (<span class="chinese-char">太初曆</span>, <em>Tàichū Lì</em>, 104 BCE) fixed the new year to the first lunar month, establishing the date for <a href="/spring-festival/">Chinese New Year</a> that persists today</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>曆法改革</strong>——太初曆（前104年）將新年定於正月，確立了沿用至今的<a href="/spring-festival/">農曆新年</a>日期</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>历法改革</strong>——太初历（前104年）将新年定于正月，确立了沿用至今的<a href="/spring-festival/">农历新年</a>日期</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Paper invention</strong> — Cai Lun (<span class="chinese-char">蔡倫</span>, <em>Cài Lún</em>) improved paper-making technology (c. 105 CE), one of the most consequential inventions in human history</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>造紙術</strong>——蔡倫（<span class="chinese-char">蔡倫</span>）改良了造紙技術（約105年），人類歷史上最重要的發明之一</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>造纸术</strong>——蔡伦（<span class="chinese-char">蔡伦</span>）改良了造纸技术（约105年），人类历史上最重要的发明之一</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong><a href="/tcm/">Medical texts</a></strong> — The <em>Huangdi Neijing</em> (<span class="chinese-char">黃帝內經</span>, <em>Huángdì Nèijīng</em>) and <em>Shennong Bencao Jing</em> (<span class="chinese-char">神農本草經</span>, <em>Shénnóng Běncǎo Jīng</em>) established the theoretical foundations of Chinese medicine</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong><a href="/tcm/">醫學典籍</a></strong>——《黃帝內經》（<span class="chinese-char">黃帝內經</span>）和《神農本草經》（<span class="chinese-char">神農本草經</span>）奠定了中醫理論基礎</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong><a href="/tcm/">医学典籍</a></strong>——《黄帝内经》（<span class="chinese-char">黄帝内经</span>）和《神农本草经》（<span class="chinese-char">神农本草经</span>）奠定了中医理论基础</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Silk Road</strong> — Zhang Qian's (<span class="chinese-char">張騫</span>, <em>Zhāng Qiān</em>) missions opened the <a href="/hanfu/">Silk Road</a> trade network, connecting China to Central Asia, Persia, and Rome</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>絲綢之路</strong>——張騫的出使開通了<a href="/hanfu/">絲綢之路</a>貿易網絡，將中國與中亞、波斯和羅馬聯繫起來</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>丝绸之路</strong>——张骞的出使开通了<a href="/hanfu/">丝绸之路</a>贸易网络，将中国与中亚、波斯和罗马联系起来</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Sima Qian's <em>Shiji</em></strong> (<span class="chinese-char">史記</span>, <em>Shǐjì</em>) — The first comprehensive Chinese history, establishing the historiographical tradition and recording the <a href="/martial-arts/#wuxia">knight-errant (<span class="chinese-char">俠</span>, <em>xiá</em>)</a> tradition</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>司馬遷《史記》</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">史記</span>）——首部綜合性中國歷史著作，確立了史學傳統並記錄了<a href="/martial-arts/#wuxia">遊俠（俠）</a>傳統</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>司马迁《史记》</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">史记</span>）——首部综合性中国历史著作，确立了史学传统并记录了<a href="/martial-arts/#wuxia">游侠（侠）</a>传统</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Astronomy</strong> — Zhang Heng (<span class="chinese-char">張衡</span>, <em>Zhāng Héng</em>) invented the armillary sphere and the world's first seismoscope, advancing the observational astronomy that informed the calendar</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>天文學</strong>——張衡（<span class="chinese-char">張衡</span>）發明了渾天儀和世界上第一台地動儀，推動了為曆法提供依據的觀測天文學</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>天文学</strong>——张衡（<span class="chinese-char">张衡</span>）发明了浑天仪和世界上第一台地动仪，推动了为历法提供依据的观测天文学</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="three-kingdoms">
      <h2>Three Kingdoms & Jin (<span class="chinese-char">三國·晉</span>, <em>Sānguó · Jìn</em>, 220–420 CE)</h2>
      <p><span class="lang-en">The fall of the Han inaugurated centuries of division. The <strong>Three Kingdoms</strong> period (220–280 CE) — Wei, Shu, and Wu — is one of the most romanticised eras in Chinese history, immortalised in the novel <em>Romance of the Three Kingdoms</em> (<span class="chinese-char">三國演義</span>, <em>Sānguó Yǎnyì</em>).</span><span class="lang-tc">漢朝滅亡開啟了數世紀的分裂。<strong>三國</strong>時期（220–280年）——魏、蜀、吳——是中國歷史上最被浪漫化的時代之一，在小說《三國演義》（<span class="chinese-char">三國演義</span>）中不朽。</span><span class="lang-sc">汉朝灭亡开启了数世纪的分裂。<strong>三国</strong>时期（220–280年）——魏、蜀、吴——是中国历史上最被浪漫化的时代之一，在小说《三国演义》（<span class="chinese-char">三国演义</span>）中不朽。</span></p>
      <h3><span class="lang-en">Cultural Contributions</span><span class="lang-tc">文化貢獻</span><span class="lang-sc">文化贡献</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong><a href="/tcm/">Zhang Zhongjing</a></strong> (<span class="chinese-char">張仲景</span>, <em>Zhāng Zhòngjǐng</em>) — His <em>Shanghan Lun</em> (<span class="chinese-char">傷寒論</span>, <em>Shānghán Lùn</em>, c. 220 CE), written during the late Han/Three Kingdoms transition, remains the most clinically influential herbal medicine text in history</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong><a href="/tcm/">張仲景</a></strong>（<span class="chinese-char">張仲景</span>）——其《傷寒論》（<span class="chinese-char">傷寒論</span>，約220年），寫於漢末三國過渡期，至今仍是歷史上臨床影響最大的中醫藥典籍</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong><a href="/tcm/">张仲景</a></strong>（<span class="chinese-char">张仲景</span>）——其《伤寒论》（<span class="chinese-char">伤寒论</span>，约220年），写于汉末三国过渡期，至今仍是历史上临床影响最大的中医药典籍</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Hua Tuo</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">華佗</span>, <em>Huà Tuó</em>) — Legendary physician who developed anaesthesia (mafeisan, <span class="chinese-char">麻沸散</span>, <em>máfèisàn</em>) and the Five Animal Frolics exercise system</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>華佗</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">華佗</span>）——傳奇名醫，發明了麻醉藥（麻沸散，<span class="chinese-char">麻沸散</span>）和五禽戲</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>华佗</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">华佗</span>）——传奇名医，发明了麻醉药（麻沸散，<span class="chinese-char">麻沸散</span>）和五禽戏</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Metaphysical philosophy</strong> — The <em>xuanxue</em> (<span class="chinese-char">玄學</span>, <em>xuánxué</em>, "dark learning") movement reinterpreted the <a href="/yijing/">Yi Jing</a> and <a href="/taoism/">Daoist</a> classics, profoundly influencing later Chinese thought</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>玄學哲學</strong>——玄學（<span class="chinese-char">玄學</span>）運動重新詮釋了<a href="/yijing/">易經</a>和<a href="/taoism/">道家</a>經典，深遠影響了後世中國思想</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>玄学哲学</strong>——玄学（<span class="chinese-char">玄学</span>）运动重新诠释了<a href="/yijing/">易经</a>和<a href="/taoism/">道家</a>经典，深远影响了后世中国思想</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Buddhism's spread</strong> — Buddhism expanded rapidly during the period of division, eventually synthesising with native Chinese traditions to create uniquely Chinese Buddhist forms</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>佛教傳播</strong>——佛教在分裂時期迅速擴張，最終與中國本土傳統融合，創造出獨特的中國佛教形式</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>佛教传播</strong>——佛教在分裂时期迅速扩张，最终与中国本土传统融合，创造出独特的中国佛教形式</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="sui-tang">
      <h2>Sui & Tang Dynasties (<span class="chinese-char">隋唐</span>, <em>Suí Táng</em>, 581–907 CE)</h2>
      <p><span class="lang-en">The <strong>Sui Dynasty</strong> (581–618) reunified China after centuries of division. The <strong>Tang Dynasty</strong> (618–907) that followed is widely regarded as the zenith of Chinese civilisation — a cosmopolitan, culturally confident empire that was the world's wealthiest and most advanced society.</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>隋朝</strong>（581–618年）在數世紀的分裂後重新統一了中國。其後的<strong>唐朝</strong>（618–907年）被廣泛認為是中華文明的巔峰——一個世界主義的、文化自信的帝國，是當時世界上最富裕、最先進的社會。</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>隋朝</strong>（581–618年）在数世纪的分裂后重新统一了中国。其后的<strong>唐朝</strong>（618–907年）被广泛认为是中华文明的巅峰——一个世界主义的、文化自信的帝国，是当时世界上最富裕、最先进的社会。</span></p>
      <h3><span class="lang-en">Cultural Contributions</span><span class="lang-tc">文化貢獻</span><span class="lang-sc">文化贡献</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>BaZi development</strong> — Li Xuzhong (<span class="chinese-char">李虛中</span>, <em>Lǐ Xūzhōng</em>) developed the <a href="/bazi/">Three Pillars</a> system of destiny analysis during the Tang, laying the groundwork for the full Four Pillars method refined in the Song</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>八字發展</strong>——李虛中（<span class="chinese-char">李虛中</span>）在唐代發展了<a href="/bazi/">三柱</a>命理分析體系，為宋代完善的四柱法奠定了基礎</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>八字发展</strong>——李虚中（<span class="chinese-char">李虚中</span>）在唐代发展了<a href="/bazi/">三柱</a>命理分析体系，为宋代完善的四柱法奠定了基础</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Poetry golden age</strong> — Li Bai (<span class="chinese-char">李白</span>, <em>Lǐ Bái</em>), Du Fu (<span class="chinese-char">杜甫</span>, <em>Dù Fǔ</em>), and Wang Wei (<span class="chinese-char">王維</span>, <em>Wáng Wéi</em>) created the pinnacle of Chinese poetic art</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>詩歌黃金時代</strong>——李白（<span class="chinese-char">李白</span>）、杜甫（<span class="chinese-char">杜甫</span>）和王維（<span class="chinese-char">王維</span>）創造了中國詩歌藝術的巔峰</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>诗歌黄金时代</strong>——李白（<span class="chinese-char">李白</span>）、杜甫（<span class="chinese-char">杜甫</span>）和王维（<span class="chinese-char">王维</span>）创造了中国诗歌艺术的巅峰</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Tang Code</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">唐律</span>, <em>Táng Lǜ</em>) — The comprehensive legal code that influenced legal systems across East Asia</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>唐律</strong>——影響了整個東亞法律體系的綜合法典</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>唐律</strong>——影响了整个东亚法律体系的综合法典</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong><a href="/hanfu/">Fashion</a></strong> — The most cosmopolitan period in Chinese clothing history, absorbing Silk Road influences into a distinctively bold aesthetic</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong><a href="/hanfu/">時尚</a></strong>——中國服飾史上最國際化的時期，將絲綢之路的影響融入獨特大膽的美學</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong><a href="/hanfu/">时尚</a></strong>——中国服饰史上最国际化的时期，将丝绸之路的影响融入独特大胆的美学</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Chan Buddhism (<span class="chinese-char">禪宗</span>, <em>Chánzōng</em>)</strong> — The Tang saw the full maturation of Chinese Buddhism, including the Chan (Zen) school and the integration of Buddhist and <a href="/taoism/">Daoist</a> thought</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>禪宗（<span class="chinese-char">禪宗</span>）</strong>——唐代見證了中國佛教的全面成熟，包括禪宗的發展和佛<a href="/taoism/">道</a>思想的融合</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>禅宗（<span class="chinese-char">禅宗</span>）</strong>——唐代见证了中国佛教的全面成熟，包括禅宗的发展和佛<a href="/taoism/">道</a>思想的融合</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong><a href="/folk-arts/">Performing arts</a></strong> — Court lion dances, music, and theatrical traditions flourished, influencing folk performance arts for centuries</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong><a href="/folk-arts/">表演藝術</a></strong>——宮廷獅舞、音樂和戲劇傳統繁榮發展，影響了數百年的民間表演藝術</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong><a href="/folk-arts/">表演艺术</a></strong>——宫廷狮舞、音乐和戏剧传统繁荣发展，影响了数百年的民间表演艺术</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong>Printing</strong> — The world's earliest known printed book (Diamond Sutra, <span class="chinese-char">金剛經</span>, <em>Jīngāng Jīng</em>, 868 CE) was produced during the Tang, beginning the revolution in information technology that would transform Chinese culture</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>印刷術</strong>——世界上已知最早的印刷書籍（《金剛經》，868年）在唐代問世，開啟了改變中國文化的資訊技術革命</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>印刷术</strong>——世界上已知最早的印刷书籍（《金刚经》，868年）在唐代问世，开启了改变中国文化的信息技术革命</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><strong><a href="/martial-arts/">Martial arts</a></strong> — The Shaolin Temple's martial tradition reached prominence after warrior monks aided Li Shimin (<span class="chinese-char">李世民</span>, <em>Lǐ Shìmín</em>) in founding the Tang Dynasty</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong><a href="/martial-arts/">武術</a></strong>——少林寺的武術傳統在武僧協助李世民建立唐朝後聲名鵲起</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong><a href="/martial-arts/">武术</a></strong>——少林寺的武术传统在武僧协助李世民建立唐朝后声名鹊起</span></li>
      </ul>

