      <h3><span class="lang-en"><em>Dream of the Red Chamber</em> and the Ming Connection</span><span class="lang-tc">《紅樓夢》與明朝的聯繫</span><span class="lang-sc">《红楼梦》与明朝的联系</span></h3>

      <p><span class="lang-en"><em>Dream of the Red Chamber</em> (<span class="chinese-char">紅樓夢</span>, <em>H&oacute;ngl&oacute;u M&egrave;ng</em>), also known as <em>The Story of the Stone</em> (<span class="chinese-char">石頭記</span>, <em>Shítou Jì</em>), is widely regarded as the greatest Chinese novel ever written. For over a century, mainstream <strong>Redology</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">紅學</span>, <em>Hóngxué</em>) has attributed its first 80 chapters to <strong>Cao Xueqin</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">曹雪芹</span>, <em>Cáo Xuěqín</em>, c. 1715&ndash;1763), a descendant of a once-powerful Qing official family. This attribution was established by the scholar <strong>Hu Shi</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">胡適</span>, <em>Hú Shì</em>) in 1921 and remains the dominant position in both Chinese and Western scholarship.</span><span class="lang-tc">《紅樓夢》（<span class="chinese-char">紅樓夢</span>），又名《石頭記》（<span class="chinese-char">石頭記</span>），被廣泛認為是中國歷史上最偉大的小說。一個多世紀以來，主流<strong>紅學</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">紅學</span>）將其前80回歸於<strong>曹雪芹</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">曹雪芹</span>，約1715–1763年），他是一個曾經權勢顯赫的清朝官宦家族的後裔。這一歸屬由學者<strong>胡適</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">胡適</span>）於1921年確立，至今仍是中西方學術界的主流觀點。</span><span class="lang-sc">《红楼梦》（<span class="chinese-char">红楼梦</span>），又名《石头记》（<span class="chinese-char">石头记</span>），被广泛认为是中国历史上最伟大的小说。一个多世纪以来，主流<strong>红学</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">红学</span>）将其前80回归于<strong>曹雪芹</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">曹雪芹</span>，约1715–1763年），他是一个曾经权势显赫的清朝官宦家族的后裔。这一归属由学者<strong>胡适</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">胡适</span>）于1921年确立，至今仍是中西方学术界的主流观点。</span></p>

      <p><span class="lang-en">However, an alternative theory has gained significant popular attention in recent years, linking the novel directly to the <strong>fall of the Ming Dynasty</strong> and the imperial Zhu family.</span><span class="lang-tc">然而，近年來一種替代理論引起了廣泛的公眾關注，將小說直接與<strong>明朝滅亡</strong>和皇室朱家聯繫起來。</span><span class="lang-sc">然而，近年来一种替代理论引起了广泛的公众关注，将小说直接与<strong>明朝灭亡</strong>和皇室朱家联系起来。</span></p>

      <div class="callout-box callout-box--jade">
        <div class="callout-icon">📖</div>
        <div class="callout-content">
          <h3><span class="lang-en">The Zhu Cizhao Theory</span><span class="lang-tc">朱慈炤理論</span><span class="lang-sc">朱慈炤理论</span></h3>
          <p><span class="lang-en">Researcher <strong>Cao Dongfang</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">曹東芳</span>, <em>Cáo Dōngfāng</em>), in collaboration with Ming-Qing historian <strong>Nan Bingwen</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">南炳文</span>, <em>Nán Bǐngwén</em>) and others, has argued that the true author of <em>Dream of the Red Chamber</em> was <strong>Zhu Cizhao</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">朱慈炤</span>, <em>Zhū Cízhào</em>), the fourth son of the <strong>Chongzhen Emperor</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">崇禎帝</span>, <em>Chóngzhēn Dì</em>) &mdash; the last ruler of the Ming Dynasty. This claim was formally presented in a letter from the <strong>Shandong Zhonglin Museum of Historical Literature</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">山東眾林文史文獻博物館</span>, <em>Shāndōng Zhònglín Wénshǐ Wénxiàn Bówùguǎn</em>) in June 2023.</span><span class="lang-tc">研究者<strong>曹東芳</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">曹東芳</span>）與明清史學家<strong>南炳文</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">南炳文</span>）等人合作，主張《紅樓夢》的真正作者是<strong>朱慈炤</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">朱慈炤</span>），<strong>崇禎帝</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">崇禎帝</span>）——明朝最後一位君主——的第四子。此說法於2023年6月由<strong>山東眾林文史文獻博物館</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">山東眾林文史文獻博物館</span>）正式提出。</span><span class="lang-sc">研究者<strong>曹东芳</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">曹东芳</span>）与明清史学家<strong>南炳文</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">南炳文</span>）等人合作，主张《红楼梦》的真正作者是<strong>朱慈炤</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">朱慈炤</span>），<strong>崇祯帝</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">崇祯帝</span>）——明朝最后一位君主——的第四子。此说法于2023年6月由<strong>山东众林文史文献博物馆</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">山东众林文史文献博物馆</span>）正式提出。</span></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h4><span class="lang-en">The Evidence Presented</span><span class="lang-tc">提出的證據</span><span class="lang-sc">提出的证据</span></h4>

      <p><span class="lang-en">Cao Dongfang&rsquo;s theory rests on several lines of argument:</span><span class="lang-tc">曹東芳的理論基於以下幾條論證線索：</span><span class="lang-sc">曹东芳的理论基于以下几条论证线索：</span></p>

      <div class="info-grid">
        <div class="info-card"><span class="info-card-icon">📜</span><div class="info-card-value"><span class="lang-en">Manuscript</span><span class="lang-tc">手稿</span><span class="lang-sc">手稿</span></div><div class="info-card-label"><span class="lang-en">Jiǎxū Edition</span><span class="lang-tc">甲戌本</span><span class="lang-sc">甲戌本</span></div><div class="info-card-desc"><span class="lang-en">Cao claims the Jiǎxū manuscript (<span class="chinese-char">甲戌本</span>, <em>Jiǎxū Běn</em>) held at the Shanghai Museum is the author&rsquo;s original, and that the black text and red annotations are in the same hand &mdash; Zhu Cizhao&rsquo;s.</span><span class="lang-tc">曹東芳主張上海博物館所藏的甲戌本（<span class="chinese-char">甲戌本</span>）是作者的原稿，且黑色正文和紅色批注出自同一人之手——朱慈炤。</span><span class="lang-sc">曹东芳主张上海博物馆所藏的甲戌本（<span class="chinese-char">甲戌本</span>）是作者的原稿，且黑色正文和红色批注出自同一人之手——朱慈炤。</span></div></div>
        <div class="info-card"><span class="info-card-icon">🏯</span><div class="info-card-value"><span class="lang-en">Palace Objects</span><span class="lang-tc">宮廷器物</span><span class="lang-sc">宫廷器物</span></div><div class="info-card-label"><span class="lang-en">Imperial Artefacts</span><span class="lang-tc">皇家文物</span><span class="lang-sc">皇家文物</span></div><div class="info-card-desc"><span class="lang-en">The novel describes Ming imperial objects &mdash; including Xuande bronzes from the Ruisi Hall (<span class="chinese-char">睿思殿</span>, <em>Ruìsī Diàn</em>) &mdash; with a specificity that suggests first-hand knowledge of the palace.</span><span class="lang-tc">小說描述了明朝宮廷器物——包括睿思殿（<span class="chinese-char">睿思殿</span>）的宣德銅器——其具體程度暗示作者對宮殿有親身了解。</span><span class="lang-sc">小说描述了明朝宫廷器物——包括睿思殿（<span class="chinese-char">睿思殿</span>）的宣德铜器——其具体程度暗示作者对宫殿有亲身了解。</span></div></div>
        <div class="info-card"><span class="info-card-icon">📅</span><div class="info-card-value"><span class="lang-en">Dating</span><span class="lang-tc">年代考證</span><span class="lang-sc">年代考证</span></div><div class="info-card-label"><span class="lang-en">Kangxi-Era Poem</span><span class="lang-tc">康熙年間詩作</span><span class="lang-sc">康熙年间诗作</span></div><div class="info-card-desc"><span class="lang-en">The latest datable reference in the text is a poem by Deng Hanyi (<span class="chinese-char">鄧漢儀</span>, <em>Dèng Hànyí</em>, d. 1689), suggesting the author lived in the late Ming/early Qing transition.</span><span class="lang-tc">文中可考的最晚時間參照是鄧漢儀（<span class="chinese-char">鄧漢儀</span>，卒於1689年）的一首詩，暗示作者生活在明末清初過渡時期。</span><span class="lang-sc">文中可考的最晚时间参照是邓汉仪（<span class="chinese-char">邓汉仪</span>，卒于1689年）的一首诗，暗示作者生活在明末清初过渡时期。</span></div></div>
        <div class="info-card"><span class="info-card-icon">🔤</span><div class="info-card-value"><span class="lang-en">Wordplay</span><span class="lang-tc">文字遊戲</span><span class="lang-sc">文字游戏</span></div><div class="info-card-label"><span class="lang-en">Coded Names</span><span class="lang-tc">隱語姓名</span><span class="lang-sc">隐语姓名</span></div><div class="info-card-desc"><span class="lang-en">Character names encode hidden meanings: &ldquo;Jiǎ&rdquo; (<span class="chinese-char">賈</span>, <em>jiǎ</em>) sounds like &ldquo;false&rdquo; (<span class="chinese-char">假</span>, <em>jiǎ</em>); &ldquo;Zhēn&rdquo; (<span class="chinese-char">甄</span>, <em>zhēn</em>) sounds like &ldquo;true&rdquo; (<span class="chinese-char">真</span>, <em>zhēn</em>); &ldquo;Zh&umacr;&rdquo; (<span class="chinese-char">珠/竹</span>, <em>zhū/zhú</em>) echoes the Ming imperial surname (<span class="chinese-char">朱</span>, <em>Zhū</em>).</span><span class="lang-tc">角色姓名蘊含隱義：「賈」（<span class="chinese-char">賈</span>）諧音「假」（<span class="chinese-char">假</span>）；「甄」（<span class="chinese-char">甄</span>）諧音「真」（<span class="chinese-char">真</span>）；「珠/竹」（<span class="chinese-char">珠/竹</span>）暗合明朝皇姓「朱」（<span class="chinese-char">朱</span>）。</span><span class="lang-sc">角色姓名蕴含隐义："贾"（<span class="chinese-char">贾</span>）谐音"假"（<span class="chinese-char">假</span>）；"甄"（<span class="chinese-char">甄</span>）谐音"真"（<span class="chinese-char">真</span>）；"珠/竹"（<span class="chinese-char">珠/竹</span>）暗合明朝皇姓"朱"（<span class="chinese-char">朱</span>）。</span></div></div>
