      <h4><span class="lang-en">Who Was Zhu Cizhao?</span><span class="lang-tc">朱慈炤是誰？</span><span class="lang-sc">朱慈炤是谁？</span></h4>

      <p><span class="lang-en"><strong>Zhu Cizhao</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">朱慈炤</span>, <em>Zhū Cízhào</em>, 1632&ndash;1708) was the fourth son of the Chongzhen Emperor and Imperial Noble Consort Tian (<span class="chinese-char">田貴妃</span>, <em>Tián Guìfēi</em>). When Beijing fell to Li Zicheng&rsquo;s (<span class="chinese-char">李自成</span>, <em>Lǐ Zìchéng</em>) rebel forces in April 1644, the 12-year-old prince was entrusted to eunuchs for evacuation before his father hanged himself at Coal Hill (<span class="chinese-char">煤山</span>, <em>Méishān</em>). According to historical records, when Li Zicheng ordered the boy to kneel, the prince defiantly replied: <span class="chinese-char">「何不殺我」</span> (&ldquo;Why don&rsquo;t you just kill me?&rdquo;).</span><span class="lang-tc"><strong>朱慈炤</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">朱慈炤</span>，1632–1708年）是崇禎帝與田貴妃（<span class="chinese-char">田貴妃</span>）所生的第四子。1644年4月北京陷落於李自成叛軍時，12歲的皇子被託付給太監疏散，而其父在煤山（<span class="chinese-char">煤山</span>）自縊殉國。據史載，李自成令該童跪下時，皇子傲然回道：<span class="chinese-char">「何不殺我」</span>。</span><span class="lang-sc"><strong>朱慈炤</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">朱慈炤</span>，1632–1708年）是崇祯帝与田贵妃（<span class="chinese-char">田贵妃</span>）所生的第四子。1644年4月北京陷落于李自成叛军时，12岁的皇子被托付给太监疏散，而其父在煤山（<span class="chinese-char">煤山</span>）自缢殉国。据史载，李自成令该童跪下时，皇子傲然回道：<span class="chinese-char">"何不杀我"</span>。</span></p>

      <p><span class="lang-en">After the Qing conquest, Zhu Cizhao lived in hiding for over 60 years under the alias <strong>Wang Shiyuan</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">王士元</span>, <em>Wáng Shìyuán</em>) &mdash; a name whose characters read backwards (<span class="chinese-char">元是王</span>, <em>yuán shì wáng</em>) mean &ldquo;was originally a king.&rdquo; He settled in Yuyao, Zhejiang (<span class="chinese-char">浙江餘姚</span>, <em>Zhèjiāng Yúyáo</em>), making his living as a schoolteacher. In <strong>1708</strong> (Kangxi 47), at age 75, he was captured, tried, and <strong>executed by lingchi</strong> with his six sons. The historian <strong>Meng Sen</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">孟森</span>, <em>Mèng Sēn</em>) later demonstrated that the Qing court had deliberately falsified records to deny his imperial identity &mdash; a deception that lasted centuries.</span><span class="lang-tc">清朝入關後，朱慈炤以化名<strong>王士元</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">王士元</span>）隱居了60多年——此名倒讀（<span class="chinese-char">元是王</span>）意為「原來是王」。他定居浙江餘姚，以教書為生。<strong>1708年</strong>（康熙四十七年），75歲的他被捕、受審，與六子一同被<strong>凌遲處死</strong>。歷史學家<strong>孟森</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">孟森</span>）後來證明清廷曾蓄意篡改記錄以否認其皇室身份——這一欺騙延續了數百年。</span><span class="lang-sc">清朝入关后，朱慈炤以化名<strong>王士元</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">王士元</span>）隐居了60多年——此名倒读（<span class="chinese-char">元是王</span>）意为"原来是王"。他定居浙江余姚，以教书为生。<strong>1708年</strong>（康熙四十七年），75岁的他被捕、受审，与六子一同被<strong>凌迟处死</strong>。历史学家<strong>孟森</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">孟森</span>）后来证明清廷曾蓄意篡改记录以否认其皇室身份——这一欺骗延续了数百年。</span></p>

      <div class="callout-box callout-box--jade">
        <div class="callout-icon">⚖️</div>
        <div class="callout-content">
          <h3><span class="lang-en">A Contested Claim</span><span class="lang-tc">一個有爭議的主張</span><span class="lang-sc">一个有争议的主张</span></h3>
          <p><span class="lang-en">It is important to note that the Zhu Cizhao authorship theory <strong>has not been endorsed</strong> by mainstream Redology institutions such as the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences&rsquo; Dream of the Red Chamber Research Institute. Detailed methodological critiques have been published, challenging the manuscript identification, the homophone-based readings, and the circular reasoning in linking the commentator &ldquo;Zhiyanzhai&rdquo; (<span class="chinese-char">脂硯齋</span>, <em>Zhīyànzhāi</em>) to the author. Over 60 alternative authorship candidates have been proposed throughout the history of Redology, and the Cao Xueqin attribution remains the scholarly consensus in both Chinese and Western academia.</span><span class="lang-tc">需要指出的是，朱慈炤作者理論<strong>未獲</strong>中國社會科學院紅樓夢研究所等主流紅學機構的認可。已有詳細的方法論批評發表，質疑手稿鑒定、諧音解讀以及將批注者「脂硯齋」（<span class="chinese-char">脂硯齋</span>）與作者關聯的循環論證。在紅學史上已提出了60多位備選作者，曹雪芹的歸屬仍是中西方學術界的共識。</span><span class="lang-sc">需要指出的是，朱慈炤作者理论<strong>未获</strong>中国社会科学院红楼梦研究所等主流红学机构的认可。已有详细的方法论批评发表，质疑手稿鉴定、谐音解读以及将批注者"脂砚斋"（<span class="chinese-char">脂砚斋</span>）与作者关联的循环论证。在红学史上已提出了60多位备选作者，曹雪芹的归属仍是中西方学术界的共识。</span></p>
          <p><span class="lang-en">We present this theory as a notable development in the ongoing Redology debate and a window into the enduring cultural significance of both <em>Dream of the Red Chamber</em> and the fall of the Ming Dynasty &mdash; not as an established conclusion.</span><span class="lang-tc">我們呈現此理論作為持續進行的紅學辯論中的一個值得關注的發展，以及洞察《紅樓夢》和明朝滅亡持久文化意義的一扇窗——而非已成定論。</span><span class="lang-sc">我们呈现此理论作为持续进行的红学辩论中的一个值得关注的发展，以及洞察《红楼梦》和明朝灭亡持久文化意义的一扇窗——而非已成定论。</span></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="timeline">
      <h2><span class="lang-en">Dynasty Timeline</span><span class="lang-tc">朝代年表</span><span class="lang-sc">朝代年表</span></h2>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item"><h3>Xia (<span class="chinese-char">夏</span>, <em>Xià</em>) — c. 2070–1600 BCE</h3><p><span class="lang-en">Calendar origins, bronze age</span><span class="lang-tc">曆法起源、青銅時代</span><span class="lang-sc">历法起源、青铜时代</span></p></div>
        <div class="timeline-item"><h3>Shang (<span class="chinese-char">商</span>, <em>Shāng</em>) — c. 1600–1046 BCE</h3><p><span class="lang-en">Oracle bones, writing, Stems & Branches</span><span class="lang-tc">甲骨文、文字、天干地支</span><span class="lang-sc">甲骨文、文字、天干地支</span></p></div>
        <div class="timeline-item"><h3>Western Zhou (<span class="chinese-char">西周</span>, <em>Xī Zhōu</em>) — 1046–771 BCE</h3><p><span class="lang-en">Yi Jing (<span class="chinese-char">易經</span>, <em>Yìjīng</em>), ritual system, Mandate of Heaven</span><span class="lang-tc">易經、禮制、天命</span><span class="lang-sc">易经、礼制、天命</span></p></div>
        <div class="timeline-item"><h3>Eastern Zhou (<span class="chinese-char">東周</span>, <em>Dōng Zhōu</em>) — 771–256 BCE</h3><p><span class="lang-en">Hundred Schools of Thought, Five Elements</span><span class="lang-tc">百家爭鳴、五行</span><span class="lang-sc">百家争鸣、五行</span></p></div>
        <div class="timeline-item"><h3>Qin (<span class="chinese-char">秦</span>, <em>Qín</em>) — 221–206 BCE</h3><p><span class="lang-en">Unification, standardisation, zodiac evidence</span><span class="lang-tc">統一、標準化、生肖證據</span><span class="lang-sc">统一、标准化、生肖证据</span></p></div>
        <div class="timeline-item"><h3>Han (<span class="chinese-char">漢</span>, <em>Hàn</em>) — 206 BCE–220 CE</h3><p><span class="lang-en">Calendar reform, Silk Road, Huangdi Neijing</span><span class="lang-tc">曆法改革、絲綢之路、黃帝內經</span><span class="lang-sc">历法改革、丝绸之路、黄帝内经</span></p></div>
        <div class="timeline-item"><h3>Three Kingdoms (<span class="chinese-char">三國</span>, <em>Sānguó</em>) — 220–280 CE</h3><p><span class="lang-en">Zhang Zhongjing, Hua Tuo, literary romance</span><span class="lang-tc">張仲景、華佗、文學傳奇</span><span class="lang-sc">张仲景、华佗、文学传奇</span></p></div>
        <div class="timeline-item"><h3>Tang (<span class="chinese-char">唐</span>, <em>Táng</em>) — 618–907 CE</h3><p><span class="lang-en">BaZi (<span class="chinese-char">八字</span>, <em>Bāzì</em>) origins, poetry, Chan Buddhism, printing</span><span class="lang-tc">八字起源、詩歌、禪宗、印刷</span><span class="lang-sc">八字起源、诗歌、禅宗、印刷</span></p></div>
        <div class="timeline-item"><h3>Song (<span class="chinese-char">宋</span>, <em>Sòng</em>) — 960–1279 CE</h3><p><span class="lang-en">BaZi perfected, Neo-Confucianism, Four Inventions</span><span class="lang-tc">八字完善、理學、四大發明</span><span class="lang-sc">八字完善、理学、四大发明</span></p></div>
        <div class="timeline-item"><h3>Yuan (<span class="chinese-char">元</span>, <em>Yuán</em>) — 1271–1368 CE</h3><p><span class="lang-en">Drama, Shoushi calendar, agricultural texts</span><span class="lang-tc">戲劇、授時曆、農學著作</span><span class="lang-sc">戏剧、授时历、农学著作</span></p></div>
        <div class="timeline-item"><h3>Ming (<span class="chinese-char">明</span>, <em>Míng</em>) — 1368–1644 CE</h3><p><span class="lang-en">Hanfu revival, Bencao Gangmu, Zheng He</span><span class="lang-tc">漢服復興、本草綱目、鄭和</span><span class="lang-sc">汉服复兴、本草纲目、郑和</span></p></div>
      </div>
    </section>

